The paper deals with the problem of adversarial attacks on deep neural networks, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields of computer science. However, the use of variational autoencoders and the focus on disentangling robust and vulnerable features suggest that the paper is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the use of game theory and the focus on detecting adversarial inputs suggest that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
